HIV/AIDS: China ta ba da rahoton karuwar kashi 14% na sabbin masu cutar
China ta ba da rahoton cewa kashi 14% na yawan al'ummarta suna rayuwa da cutar kanjamau.
Fiye da mutane 820,000 ne cutar ta shafa a kasar, a cewar jami'an lafiya.
An bayar da rahoton kusan sabbin shari'o'i 40,000 a cikin kwata na ƙarshe na 2018.
Yawancin sababbin lokuta ana ɗaukar su ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya bambanta da na baya.
A halin yanzu, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin sakamakon gurbataccen jini.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar kanjamau ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'in kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taron manema labarai a lardin Yunnan.
Koyaya, kowace shekara, yawan mutanen da ke da cutar kanjamau a China ya karu da 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i ta zama babbar matsala a cikin al'ummar LGBT a China.
A shekarar 1997, an haramta yin luwadi a China, amma nuna bambanci ga LGBT ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Saboda ra'ayoyin da ake da su a kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70-90% na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza a karshe sun auri mata.
Dalilin da ya sa aka ci gaba da ɗaukar marasa lafiya shine yawanci rashin lafiyar da ake yi a cikin waɗannan ɗakunan.
Tun a shekarar 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin HIV ga jama'a a matsayin wani ɓangare na magance matsalar.
